Need to Know Info

Nuclear power plants today rely on fission to create energy(3), In a fission reactions atoms are split with the goal to release energy. A fission reaction could look like this:(3)

Kr-92 & Ba-141 are byproducts of the fission reaction, this splitting must be controlled to prevent Accidents(3)(2)

Pros of using Nuclear Power:

  • Less deaths are caused compared to other energy methods(2).
  • Less greenhouse emissions compared to even solar or wind(1).
  • High Energy Density, A kilogram of uranium can produce as much electricity as thousands of kilograms of coal(2).

Cons of using Nuclear Power:

  • Upfront Costs are higher than gas or coal power plants(2).
  • Accidents like Chernobyl make the public fear that future accidents may occur so safety is strict in most areas(2).
  • Nuclear Waste Disposal is a big reason against nuclear power and is still a concern(2).

Nuclear Power Summary

Cleanest sources of energy.png

Are you convinced?

Yes, nuclear power has a expensive up front cost, but the cost of operation and lower environmental impact make me hopeful nuclear energy can replace coal power plants(1). Nuclear power plants also provide more energy than wind or solar(4), making it easier to replace a coal plant with than wind or solar.
The safety concerns aren't a major problem for me as data shows nuclear power plants actually result in less deaths than either coal or gas plants even more so if you account how their carbon emissions kill even more.(2)
